# Layout Components

## Available Layouts

### 1. DashboardLayout

Main layout for authenticated pages with sidebar and breadcrumbs.

**Usage:**

```vue
<template>
  <DashboardLayout :breadcrumbs="breadcrumbItems">
    <!-- Your page content here -->
  </DashboardLayout>
</template>

<script setup lang="ts">
import DashboardLayout from "@/layouts/DashboardLayout.vue";
import type { BreadcrumbEntry } from "@/layouts/DashboardLayout.vue";

const breadcrumbItems: BreadcrumbEntry[] = [
  { text: "Users", isCurrent: true, href: "/admin/users" },
];

// Or with multiple breadcrumbs
const breadcrumbs: BreadcrumbEntry[] = [
  { text: "Home", href: "/admin" },
  { text: "Servers", href: "/admin/servers" },
  { text: "Edit", isCurrent: true },
];
</script>
```

**Features:**

- Collapsible sidebar (AppSidebar)
- Breadcrumb navigation
- MacDock component
- Footer
- Responsive design

### 2. AuthLayout

Layout for authentication pages (login, register, etc.)

**Usage:**

```vue
// In route definition { path: "/auth", component: () =>
import("@/layouts/AuthLayout.vue"), children: [ { path: "login", name: "Login",
component: () => import("@/pages/auth/Login.vue") }, { path: "register", name:
"Register", component: () => import("@/pages/auth/Register.vue") }, ], } //
Content is rendered via
<router-view />
```

**Features:**

- Centered card layout
- Theme toggle button
- Background picker
- App logo display
- Responsive auth forms

### 3. ErrorLayout

Layout for error pages (404, 500, etc.)

## Breadcrumbs

### BreadcrumbEntry Interface

```typescript
export interface BreadcrumbEntry {
  text: string; // Display text
  href?: string; // Link (optional for current page)
  isCurrent?: boolean; // Is this the current page?
}
```

### Breadcrumb Examples

```typescript
// Single breadcrumb (current page)
const breadcrumbs = [{ text: "Users", isCurrent: true, href: "/admin/users" }];

// Multiple breadcrumbs
const breadcrumbs = [
  { text: "Dashboard", href: "/admin" },
  { text: "Servers", href: "/admin/servers" },
  { text: "Edit Server", isCurrent: true },
];

// Dynamic breadcrumbs
const breadcrumbs = computed(() => [
  { text: "Users", href: "/admin/users" },
  { text: user.value?.username || "Loading...", isCurrent: true },
]);
```

## Page Structure with Layout

```vue
<template>
  <DashboardLayout :breadcrumbs="breadcrumbs">
    <div class="min-h-screen bg-background">
      <!-- Loading State -->
      <div v-if="loading" class="flex items-center justify-center py-12">
        <div
          class="animate-spin rounded-full h-6 w-6 border-2 border-primary"
        ></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Error State -->
      <div v-else-if="error" class="text-center py-12">
        <p class="text-red-500">{{ error }}</p>
        <Button class="mt-4" @click="retry">Try Again</Button>
      </div>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div v-else class="p-6">
        <!-- Your content -->
      </div>
    </div>
  </DashboardLayout>
</template>
```

